08/10/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri on Tuesday (7 October) issued formal invitations to the leaders of Serbia-Montenegro and Kosovo to send delegations to internationally-sponsored talks in Vienna. NATO Secretary General Lord George Robertson, EU security chief Javier Solana, and OSCE Chairman-in-Office Jaap de Hoop Scheffer will attend the meeting on 14 October. Members of the Contact Group -- consisting of the United States, the United Kingdom, Germany, France, Italy, and Russia -- have also been invited to attend. Bulgaria weighed in on the talks Tuesday, urging Kosovo and Serbia to begin discussing issues of mutual interest as soon as possible. (Trud, 24 Chassa - 08/10/03; AFP, BTA, BNT - 07/10/03)
